Rogue Cabal Doc

Rogues are split up into 3 seperate Cabals: Assassin, Basher,
and Thieves. All Cabals can practice every power, but only
the Cabal that power was designed for can practice it more
then once. Until a Rogue chooses a Cabal with "setrogue"
(help setrogue for more info), that Rogue can only practice
a power once.

|WKUAssassin|000
The Assassin Cabal is the hitmen of the Rogues. Their purpose
is to get in without being seen, do as much damage as they
can to their target, hopefully killing it, and then get out.

|WKUBasher|000
The Basher Cabal is more of a bouncer, brute force type of
Rogue. He isn't subtle about what he's trying to do, and
would rather take someone on head-on. He has spent enough
time around the other Cabals though to make him tricky,
and not just some mindless Fighter.

|WKUThieves|000
As the name implies, the Thief Cabal's purpose is to rob, cheat,
and steal whatever the Rogues need. The Thieves may not make
the best fighters, but when cornered, they do have a few
options available to them.
